TYPE
~~~~
The unit also contains a special type called AESTRING, which equals:

	aestring= string[AEMAXCHARS];

This is because the maximum string size /X can currently handle is 200, if
you go beyond this range, you will corrupt memory. So that's why I made a 
new type define so that the compiler won't allow you to send larger strings.


VARS
~~~~

There are only 2 variables that are of any importance to the outside world.
These are: AEDBase and LC. The first is pretty self-explanatory I think.
The LC one is a boolean used to inform your program of a LOST CARRIER. It is
only set/cleared when using input functions, currently only GetStr(), HotKey()
and Prompt(). Please check this one after receiving input!



INTERFACE
~~~~~~~~~

The names of the functions/procedures are equal to those of the AEDoor.library
so for more info on how it works, READ DA AUTODOCS!
The only function not contained in the library is: CreateLink(). This one will
automatically establish a connection with /X, without you having to worry 
about passing the node number to the CreateComm() lib call.


NOTE: Please be very careful with string operations! Be sure to re-read yar
      pascal docs about the difference between C & Pascal strings!!!
      All /X strings are C strings, so you need to do a CtoPas() conversion
      on strings received from /X. The functions/procedures use Pascal strings
      to make it easier for you. So you can use a simple WriteStr(d,'text',LF)
      Have a look at the example files if this is too confusing :)


Here's the interface section of the unit:


function CreateLink: pointer;
function CreateComm (node: longint): pointer;
procedure DeleteComm (dif: pointer);

procedure SendCmd
		(dif: pointer;
		command: longint);

procedure SendStrCmd	
		(dif: pointer;
		command: longint;
		string_: aestring);

procedure SendDataCmd	
		(dif: pointer;
		command,
		data: longint);

procedure SendStrDataCmd
		(dif: pointer;
		command: longint;
		string_: aestring;
		data: longint);

function GetData (dif: pointer): plongint;
function GetString (dif: pointer): strptr;

procedure Prompt	
		(dif: pointer;
		length: longint;
		pstring: aestring);

procedure WriteStr	
		(dif : pointer;
		 string_: aestring;
		 feed: longint);

procedure ShowGFile	
		(dif: pointer;
		file_: aestring);

procedure ShowFile	
		(dif: pointer;
		file_: aestring);

procedure SetDT		
		(dif: pointer;
		id: longint;
		str: aestring);

procedure GetDT		
		(dif: pointer;
		id: longint;
		str: aestring);

procedure GetStr	
		(dif: pointer;
		length: longint;
		defstr: aestring);

function Hotkey		
		(dif: pointer;
		promptstr: aestring): char;




